      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:53:2",
      "text": [
        " أَرْبَعَةٍ شَهِدُوا عَلَى رَجُلٍ مُحْصَنٍ بِالزِّنَى ثُمَّ رَجَعَ أَحَدُهُمْ بَعْدَ مَا قُتِلَ الرَّجُلُ قَالَ إِنْ قَالَ الرَّابِعُ وَهَمْتُ ضُرِبَ الْحَدَّ وَ غُرِّمَ الدِّيَةَ وَ إِنْ قَالَ تَعَمَّدْتُ قُتِلَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Mahboub, from one of his companion, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding four who testified upon a married man with the adultery. Then one of them retracted after the man had been killed. He<sup>asws</sup> said : ‘If the fourth one says, ‘I was delusional’, he would be struck the legal penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>), and fined the wergild. And if he says, ‘I was deliberate’, he would be killed’."
        ]
      }
    },
